[SN]TITLE[SN]
Three men charged with stealing bus in Coseley

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Three Black Country men have been charged with stealing a bus from a depot which led to a police chase.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The bus was reported stolen in Coseley at about 21:40 BST on Wednesday and spotted near Albrighton at 02:40 on Thursday.
Following a police pursuit, the bus was stopped just after 03:00.
Peter Loveland, 39, Thomas Tibbs, 20, and John Burton, 38, were charged with aggravated vehicle taking and are due before Sandwell magistrates on Friday.
